title.narrative: 3.3 MCH AND NUTRITION SERVICES

description.narrative: The Government, CSOs and the private sector have access to information mechanisms to monitor bottleneck on MCH, mobilize demand for quality public health and nutrition services, which contributes to Climate Change, Disaster Risks And Envionmental Degradation, Early Detection And Treatment Of Malnutrition, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Health Systems Strengthening, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Infant And Young Child Feeding, Maternal And Newborn Health, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Nutrition â€“ General, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, children, particularly thosed aged 0-5, and prgnant women have increased access to quality health and nutrition services, healthy lifestyles and rearing practices that allow children to fully develop
